<Base title="SocialProof for Senior Care Services — Family Testimonials That Build Trust | SocialProof" description="Senior care agencies and in-home care providers: collect family testimonials that ease the most difficult decision families make. Build the trust that wins care placements.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Senior Care Services
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Families choosing care for an elderly parent are making the most emotionally charged decision of their lives. They're scared of making a mistake, wracked with guilt, and comparing every provider obsessively. Family testimonials from people who have been in that exact position are the most powerful trust-building tool available.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Speaking to the family decision-maker</h2>
      <p>The person searching for senior care is usually an adult child — often stressed, possibly long-distance, carrying enormous emotional weight. Your testimonials should speak to them: the peace of mind they found, the care their parent received, the communication that kept them informed. That's what converts a search visit into a call.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Senior care testimonials that earn trust</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Peace of mind:</strong> "I'm 800 miles away. Knowing someone reliable is with my mom every day lets me sleep at night."</li>
        <li><strong>Caregiver quality:</strong> "The caregiver became part of our family. My dad actually lights up when she arrives."</li>
        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> "They called me after every visit with an update. I never had to wonder how Dad was doing."</li>
        <li><strong>Difficult transition:</strong> "My mother refused help for years. Within a week she was comfortable and even happier."</li>
        <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> "Same caregiver every time. That consistency made all the difference for someone with dementia."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">When to collect family testimonials</h2>
      <p>Ask after the first 30 days of care — when families have seen consistent quality and the anxiety of the initial transition has eased. A brief email with your SocialProof collection link, acknowledging the difficult journey they've been on, gets high response rates. Display testimonials prominently on your services page and contact page.</p>

      <div style="background:#f0f7ff;border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;margin-top:3rem;text-align:center;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.8rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Build the trust families need to say yes</h2>
        <p style="color:#555;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Free forever for 1 active widget. No credit card required.</p>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" style="background:#2563eb;color:white;padding:0.9rem 2rem;border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;font-size:1.1rem;">Get Started Free</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
